// Semantic direction:
// programsyntese automatically generates code satisfying a spec from examples, types, or formal constraints.
// pbe_syntese (Programming by Example) generalizes from inndata/utdata pairs to a general program.
// pbe_verifiser checks each pbe_kandidat against all spec_eksempel before accepting it.
// pbe_rangér orders candidates by simplicity (Occam's razor) and coverage.
// type_hull is a typed "hole" in a program that the synthesizer must fill.
// agda_styrt uses Agda-style elaboration to guide synthesis from type information.
// observasjons_ekvivalens prunes the search space by identifying programs with identical outputs on all examples.
// cegis_loop (Counterexample-Guided Inductive Synthesis) iterates: synthesize → verify → if counterexample: add to spec.
// cegis_lerner produces candidate programs; cegis_verifiserer proves or disproves correctness.
// llm_kode_gen uses a language model to propose code from naturlig_språk descriptions.
// in_context_eksempler are few-shot demonstrations prepended to the LLM prompt.
// filter_og_rangér runs synthesized candidates through the oracle and ranks survivors.
// skisse_programmering lets the user write incomplete programs with hull that synthesis fills.
// hull_begrensning is a user-provided constraint narrowing the hull_kandidat search space.
// migreringssyntese generates transformation code to update code between API versions.
// api_adaptasjon synthesizes adapter functions between incompatible interface contracts.

// Primitive flow:
// PBE: spec = [{inn: [1,2,3], ut: 6}, {inn: [4,5], ut: 9}]
//   pbe_syntese: prøv λ l -> sum(l), λ l -> fold(+, 0, l), ...
//   pbe_verifiser hvert: består begge? -> pbe_rangér -> returner enkleste
// CEGIS: spec = sum skal være assosiativ
//   cegis_lerner: foreslå impl -> cegis_verifiserer: SMT-sjekk
//   moteksempel funnet: legg til spec -> ny iterasjon -> konvergerer
// skisse: bruker skriver: fn sorter(l) { l.___() } -- hull = ___
//   hull_kontekst: l : Liste[Heltall], forventet: sortert liste
//   hull_løs: finn alle metoder på Liste[Heltall] som returnerer Liste[Heltall]
//   -> rangér etter semantisk passende -> fyll "sorter" -> hull_fullføring
// LLM: naturlig_språk "reversér en liste uten å bruke innebygde funksjoner"
//   -> llm_kode_gen(kontekst + in_context_eksempler) -> kandidat_kode
//   -> filter_og_rangér mot test_suite -> bestemsegodkjent kandidat

// This defines program synthesis: PBE, type-driven hole-filling, CEGIS, LLM-based
// generation with filtering, sketch-based programming, and migration synthesis.
